{"id":"fish-pools","term":"Fish-pools","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Song of Solomon 7:4\">Cant. 7:4</a>) should be simply “pools,” as in the Revised Version. The reservoirs near Heshbon (q.v.) were probably stocked with fish (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 2:13\">2 Sam. 2:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 4:12\">4:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 7:3\">Isa. 7:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 22:9\">22:9</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 22:11\">11</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Song of Solomon 7:4","2 Samuel 2:13","2 Samuel 4:12","Isaiah 7:3","Isaiah 22:9","Isaiah 22:11"]}